[{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Pages = [\"index.md\"]\nDepth = 2","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"-","title":"-","text":"Modules = [FinanceTools]\nPrivate = false\nPages = [\"fracdiff.jl\", \"labeling.jl\", \"bars.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"#FinanceTools.dollarbars-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"-","title":"FinanceTools.dollarbars","text":"Calculates dollar bars with a constant amount of dollars per bar.  Input is a dataframe in the following order: Time, Price, Volume\n\nOutput is a dataframe in the following order: Time, Open, High, Low, Close, Volume\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nmethod : chooses the mode used to generate dollar bars, \"constant\" is set by default and \"SMA\", \"EMA\" will be implemented later on.\nthreshold : threshold for the dollar accumulator, a new candle will be produced when the cumulative dollar amount exceeds this number. \nfrequency : not used\nwindowlen : not used\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#FinanceTools.volumebars-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"-","title":"FinanceTools.volumebars","text":"Calculates volume bars with a constant volume per bar.  Input is a dataframe in the following order: Time, Price, Volume\n\nOutput is a dataframe in the following order: Time, Open, High, Low, Close, Volume\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nmethod : chooses the mode used to generate volume bars, \"constant\" is set by default and \"SMA\", \"EMA\" will be implemented later on.\nthreshold : threshold for the volume accumulator, a new candle will be produced when the cumulative volume exceeds this number. \nfrequency : not used\nwindowlen : not used\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
